The murder of the Free State farm manager, Brendin Horner has left the town of Senekal tense. His father, Robert Horner speaks out. Courtesy of #DStv403 SENEKAL - The father of Brendin Horner said he is disgusted that killers targeted his son. The murder of the Free State farm manager has left the town of Senekal tense. IN PICS: Tensions high in Senekal Robert Horner said, "why didn't they come and fetch me? I'm an old man." The father explained he thought something was wrong when Horner went missing for several hours after helping him with some car trouble. Various politicians and organisations gathered in the town on Friday as racial tensions threatened to spill over.